text: Vietnamese fusion restaurant with a funky atmosphere. Friendly and fast service, flavourful food and generous cocktails. Lots of vegetarian and vegan options as well. Overall, really happy with my meal here. The vegan banh mi burger is indulgent and flavourful (split it with a friend as a starter). I had the Mee Kola noodles which are on the sweeter side and definitely satisfying.

The food and drinks were really yummy and comforting to the stomach! The service was excellent and the employees were really helpful and friendly! I really liked the decoration and vibe of the place (really felt cozy). I will comeback here again :)

The cocktail drinks are excellent here. We came as a group of friends for the ramen festival and tried their Cheesy Ramen, which turned out to be amazing. It was a brothless ramen that had cheese sauce and had toppings of cheese curd with fish tofu. It was quite spicy but so good it made you want to continue eating despite the spice. The drinks, my husband and I ordered the C'est Sak√© √áa with was quite nice with a frothy top and a nice scent of lime. Boisson d'avril had a nice orange base with a nice kick of Tabasco sauce that went well with the Amaretto. Meanwhile, the Tofu fa was a boozy ginger ale with a hint of maple syrup. The bartender also offered our group some shots of green tea whisky which was quite refreshing. Be prepared for a bit of a wait if you come at their busier time, this place is quite popular.

The overall experience was positive and I'm glad I tried it, but ultimately not special enough for a second visit in my opinion. I ordered Imperial rolls, the lobster ramen Mac'n'cheese, the sate drip poutine and the Flintstone pho. My major complaint was that it simply wasn't enough food. The waiters touted it to be some behemoth amount of food, but in reality one dish per person wasn't enough (which would normally be ok if 1. The amount of food wasn't hyped and 2. The price wasn't so high). We shared the dishes among 3 people, and we were still very much hungry after. The second problem was that the food was not hot. The poutine and ramen dishes weren't even hot enough to melt the cheese. It took a while for the food to come out so I'm thinking they might have just sat at the counter for a while before coming. Either way, it lead to a less than ideal tasting experience. My favorite dish was the Sate drip poutine, the sauce was unique and had some Hawaiian flavors to it. I just wish it was hotter. The Flintstone pho wasn't a regular pho on "crack" as the menu puts it. It was missing the flavors that an actual pho place would give you. Yes they gave you an extra meat bone, but my complaint for pho was never the amount of meat.
FANTASTIC!!! Really interesting, balanced flavors, rich and satisfying without being too heavy. Service was great too - helpful, informative, and warm. Wish I could eat here all the time!

When there with gf, It's been an awesome experience to taste a Vietnamese version of poutine which is not very easy to do.  But this restaurant did an amazing job to combine both Vietnam and Quebec cuisine.  I strongly recommend coming in.

Really nice atmosphere to enjoy cozy food and drinks. They serve some traditional vietnamese dishes with a modern twist. They serve award winning poutine which are definitely worth the try. Highly recommend!

We waited for 45min before getting the food. The taste was alright, I really liked a special dish they had which was fried mussels with rice and fries, beautiful presentation as well. The pho was pretty plain, not much flavour compared to other restaurants and the beef was not easy to chew. Very nice vibe though!

Have been there only once, but ordered for take out many times, and I just love their 2 specialty poutines and their pandan cr√®me br√ªl√©e! These are their must try items if you have not tried them yet. Service is good and they put nice music. However, I can't give a perfect score because their bowl of pho that was disappointing: came lukewarm, very small portion for the price (for comparison: you pay more than what you would have paid for an XL bowl in a regular Vietnamese restaurant, but you only get about the 1/3 of the size of an XL bowl) and was lacking flavours. Bottom line: try their fusion food, they are sooo good; but you might find their traditional Vietnamese dishes so-so if you are Vietnamese/Vietnamese food connoisseur.

Amazing experience, the owner is a gem and the food is flavorful and very original. The cocktails are delicious, definitely try the sake and also the ginger ones. This is the only asian fusion restaurant that i love.
I love everything about this place - from the decor, the music, the service, and THE FOOD. üòç Like wow. Great portions for the price. Rose straight to the top of my list of places to recommend.

This place is trendy and offers fusion dishes, yet keeps its tasty traditional flavors. Definitely one of the best pho broths I've had! The terrasse is open as of 5pm and has plenty of space and some good music that's not too loud. Pictured are the pho and the bol LBT. Also had an amazing ceviche the second time I visited.

The food was wow! Love the creativity with flavors. The Kimcheesy did not disappoint and was spicy enough to make the flavors pop! Imperial rolls abd burger were bomb as well! Amazing and friendly service by Mike! Felt extremely taken care of and did shots together! ü§ó üíØ

Been to their 1st and 2nd location. Always adding seasonal favourites, and the oldies are goodies still. Service is excellent. Walked in with my cousin, sat us immediately, portions were generous and delicious, and the drinks weren't too expensive. Ambiance is cool n the playlist is poppin. Had a great time.

So you're looking for the best poutine in town? And you want to pair it with delicious drinks and appetizers? And you also want great staff and ambiance?! Then you're looking at the right place! Kimcheesy poutine is easily top 5 best things to order in the city. IN. THE. CITY! Don't skip on this one! (Also the pho is delicious, well, everything is.... Enjoy and thank me later!)

This place is a MUST !!  What's not to love ?!?  The food is excellent and full of flavors. You have dishes that varies form traditional Tonkinese soup to crazy popcorn chicken poutine or ramen cheese.  And the service .. wow !!!!  The staff is super friendly, full of energy and super helpful. They will make sure you are having a great meal and time.   And to top it all off, their drinks are great , ambiance trendy and cool and decor .. instagrammy üòù

This place has awesome food, servers and the ambiance is perfect!!! I know it's just details but when you go in the restrooms the stall have each been decorated in different fashion that is different from one another XD

All of their recipes are absolute bomb, but the portions are awfully small. You'd expect to be able to feed a full grown adult with those prices. But even a mouse would starve on how little they hand out.

Very friendly staff... the food was grate.. Usually I'm not a fan of the Vietnamese cuisine. But the eggplant salad was delicious, the shrimp pad sew was tasty and the mee kalo great!! Definitely my favorite Vietnamese  restaurant!!

I have now been a few times to La Belle Tonkinoise and their food is delicious. They always have good music playing. But the best part is the service. They always asked for my name and remembered it throughout my meal. Great way to make the clients feel special! I highly recommend it if you want very tasty vietnamese food.

Quality and tasty food. Must try : their Poutine Dac Biet (they won the Poutine Week for a reason!) and their Chicken Burger BanhMi.
(Also in the picture : Small Pho Dat Biet, chicken Popcorn, potato salad)
I ordered to pick up and the food was ready right on time. The staff : overly friendly and they make you feel like you are their friends and always welcome in the restaurant.
Yes it is pricey, but it's worth.
Let's help our local businesses!

It looks promising at first with their orignal menu offering but we were disappointed.
Great restaurants start with mastering the basics first. To show the chef‚Äôs unique skills Pad Thai and Pho. We had the Pad Thai and were disappointed with their modification of what defines Thai cuisine.
So when we had the poutine with Pho beef and Ramen noodles with cheese like Kraft‚Äôs Macaroni and cheese flavours were too spicy hot that kills the uniqueness of cheddar and umami flavour.
The poutine sauce was too salty and the preserved pink onions overtakes the origin of a poutine. Yet this poutine was un competition for Poutine week.
Perhaps this could have been a bad day by the chefs but it‚Äô still a disappintement.

Wow wow wow ! Everything was AMAZING üî• it‚Äôs crazy how it taste like actual Pho, desserts are delicious ü§§ the staffs were so friendly and sweet & we felt really welcomed
It‚Äôs was worth coming here üòã
Perfect service, staff is super nice. The food is amazing, so good and fresh. The place it self is so cool and old-school.

update2020:
lovely as always. you won‚Äôt regret coming here ;) staff and owner are nice and welcoming. loved the ambiance, the decor and the music. they also thought to put speakers outside for the terrasse in summer which is pretty nice and thoughtful. we ordered the famous poutine dac biet. this dish is pretty good. it tastes exactly like a pho but instead of noodles you get fries. their cooking is interesting because they mix two cultural dish and combine them. at first it tasted a bit weird but once you get used to it: it‚Äôs pretty awesome!
FYI a bit too salty for my taste next dish is the.. i forgot the name but it was rice with beef and red cabbage. it was ok. i prefer the poutine. FYI their menu changes often and they also have two dishes of the day that varies. overall five star because the ambiance and food/music diversity were everything. take the time to look around and notice the little details of their decor.

Delicious and would 100% go back! Friday night around 7 wasn‚Äôt too busy so reservation wasn‚Äôt necessary. Really cool environment and great and helpful staff. The food was AMAZING and service was quick! Easily one of the best speciality poutines I‚Äôve ever had. Do yourself a favour and try this place!

Great quality. Friendly staff.
Pretty expensive for what you're getting even though it's good food.
This one on of my top restaurants ever. We dine in our take out at this place evey month and we can't get enough! Especially the kimcheesy poutine üòç

Delicious takeout experience! First let‚Äôs start by the fact we can now deliver wine, just fantastic and the La belle tonki wine selection is fantastic. Decided on the Christina Gruner-Veltliner 2019 was deliciously fruity and fresh! Loved it! Took the potato salad, the flavours are delicious and the texture is simply perfect with the crunch! 7$ is pricey, but it was delicious. The katsu curry was as delicious as the rest. Chicken was still crispy for delivery, flavours was a perfect match with the wine. Sauce is flavourful and the ginger gave a nice punch! For a first experience with La Belle Tonki, would for sure recommend and would love to go back for a sit-in experience once this pandemic is over!!

Okay. This is no comfort food. Pho was simply...not good. I am sorry, sincerely. I believe it is to the taste of caucasian palette at this point. Overpriced everything. I personally wouldn't recommend this place. I feel the cook might have changed ? My friend had the Pho Poutine...I simply have no more comments.
One of the rare place where you feel home. Food is amazing and staff super friendly!
Nothing but great vibes here. Original food with insanely great FLAVOUR. Staff is young and fun. A must spot to hit when you‚Äôre in Montreal. The chef is a genius in his craft.
Absolutely on point, from the service, to the food, to the setting. This place won me over, highly recommended.

Loved this place. Very unique vietnamese fusion restaurant. Food is good and excellent price. Service is great and I feel very welcome every time I come here. I recommand the kimchi poutine and the burger !
Enjoyed everything from the entr√©es to the main dishes. Will definitely return. The place offers vegetarian and vegan options.

My favourite restaurant of all time. The staff is always the friendliest, the vibes is super chill and the food is the amazing thing you‚Äôll ever get to try. Their menu is super innovative and always right on. Make sure you try the Poutine Dac Biet! They also have many vegetarian/vegan options that are just as good. Their drinks are also very good and nice renditions to Asian desserts.

Took PHO GA on take out. Got home and realized that I totally upset the containers in the bag while bringing them home. Took them out of bag and everything was still perfectly sealed. I appreciate that they use good sealing containers!
Great meal and great service, highly recommend. thanks!

The toilets  are clean but only two available is not enough for evenings when the restaurant is full. The personal is young but polite, attentive, and fast, even in a very stressful day.  The food should be also good as they have so many online orders.

Visited while in town on a recommendation from a friend, and couldn‚Äôt have had a better experience!
The service was friendly and prompt, and the food was amazing! Loved the precautions for keeping customers save as well!
Will definitely be back next time we‚Äôre in the area!

Absolute favorite restaurant in Montreal. If I have to choose the restaurant for the night, I always take people here. The food is amazing and creative and fun - the kimcheesy poutine is my and everyone else's #1 in MT. The vibe is 10/10. Don't hesitate, eat here.

Kimcheesy poutine was great! Sauce is soooo yummy. The pho-style poutine (dac biet) was also interesting and tasty, but just a classic pho probably would've been better. Kinda bummed they don't twice-fry their fries, though, and curds were annoyingly small (but they were plentiful). Portion size is appropriate, but for the same price you'll get double the quantity elsewhere. Cr√®me br√ªl√©e was delicious perfection, the pandan really adds a beautiful twist on the traditional dessert. Ambience was festive and a bit on the loud side, but unpretentious, although I do wonder why there's manga on the wall. I'll undoubtedly be back soon!

I've been there back when it was a decent BYOB Vietnamese joint, then went back a couple of years later. What a surprise! They truly did something great and unique with this place. The daily specials are always interesting, as are the cocktails. And I really like that they kept the more "traditional" dishes on the menu. There's something for everyone. Then there's the service. Always nice and personalized. And the decor! Really a place to try.

That place is a must to go. The menu is so creative and so cool. I am not a poutine lover but I tried their poutine, Asian style and their pho, Khmer style. It was great. So tasty. Just a word : WOW. Because of Covid, and even if we can eat inside or in the terrace, we took out and it took 10 to 15 between the order and the moment we got the food, so fast !!! I will definitely come back.

Rarely am I as delighted by a restaurant experience as I was with La Belle Tonkinoise. The atmosphere is dim, funky, and cool - feels like you are somewhere exclusive. The staff are incredibly friendly, make you feel very welcome. The food is excellent, and they have some innovative dishes on a rotating menu. And best of all, the prices are great. Fantastic experience overall
One of my favourite places in Montreal. Flavour explosions in all their fusion meals and amazing friendly atmosphere. Have had many great meals from here. Highly recommend the "Funky" poutines.

This restaurant has a handful of great vegan friendly dishes. Their imperial were nice. I had the vegan tonkinoise soup and it was honestly great; you can tell that they take their time in making the broth and putting together the right vegetables, noodles, etc. In addition to all this, I also had the vegan general tao which was a big "no no". The tofu was overly crispy and the sauce wasn't mixed in properly. The service was however superb. I'm a water junkie and the staff was very accommodating. I would definitely recommend this joint. I was not able to do a bathroom check but the music and decor in the background was happening.

I was really surprised by this place. I live just a few streets away and was never compelled to try it by the looks of it on the outside. It's a really welcome addition to an otherwise pretty boring area of Villeray. The decor inside is trendy and comfy. The staff is super friendly and the food was amazing. It's a good little date spot or a cool place for a 5 √† 7.

One of my favorite restaurants.  The staff is really friendly.  The food is great; very tasty and the chef uses the freshest ingredients.  What more can I say?  The restaurant even hosted a Make your own Spring Roll workshop which I attended.  The location is superb, only a few steps away from Fabre Metro Station - super convenient. Wow! Ordered for the whole family and everything came neatly packed and labeled, so no confusion. The meal was fantastic. Burger, kimcheesy poutine and ramen were top notch. The fried tofu was fantastic, I love a good vegetarian option! 5 stars and more, definitely returning!

Delivery: ordered their poutine week submission and it was great. I don't even like Kimchi and it was still an amazing blend of flavours. Also tried their previous braised beef poutine which was pretty good.

A tad pricey for the size, but a taste that makes up for it. The poutine dac biet has such a fresh flavour with the squeeze of lime that I was absolutely amazed.   The poutine kimcheesy was sweet and added a great crisp with the chicken that again I was in awe.
Amazing ! People there are so welcoming and nice... what about the food ! Unbelievable tasty and full of flavors ! Definitely a place to try if you are in the area and you love asian comfort food !

Oh my goodness, this place is awesome. Don‚Äôt judge by the name or fa√ßade, it‚Äôs so different and cooler than your typical fusion place. Would highly recommend their fried chicken burgers, their poutines, and their ramen right now while they are still on the menu. But do try them all ;)
